Deploy the applications:
```bash
kubectl apply -f app-v1.yaml
Verify deployments:

kubectl get pods -n microservices
Check that each pod has 2 containers (application + Istio sidecar):

kubectl get pods -n microservices -o jsonpath='{range .items[*]}{.metadata.name}{"\t"}{.spec.containers[*].name}{"\n"}{end}'
Step 4: Deploy Second Version for Traffic Splitting
Create app-v2.yaml:

apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: backend-v2
  namespace: microservices
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: backend
      version: v2
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: backend
        version: v2
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: backend
        image: hashicorp/http-echo
        args:
        - "-text=Backend v2 - New Features!"
        - "-listen=:8080"
        ports:
        - containerPort: 8080
Deploy v2:

kubectl apply -f app-v2.yaml
kubectl get pods -n microservices
Task 2: Configure Traffic Routing
Step 1: Create Gateway for External Access
Create gateway.yaml:

apiVersion: networking.istio.io/v1beta1
kind: Gateway
metadata:
  name: microservices-gateway
  namespace: microservices
spec:
  selector:
    istio: ingressgateway
  servers:
  - port:
      number: 80
      name: http
      protocol: HTTP
    hosts:
    - "*"
Apply the gateway:

kubectl apply -f gateway.yaml
Step 2: Configure Destination Rules
Create destination-rules.yaml:

apiVersion: networking.istio.io/v1beta1
kind: DestinationRule
metadata:
  name: backend-destination
  namespace: microservices
spec:
  host: backend
  subsets:
  - name: v1
    labels:
      version: v1
  - name: v2
    labels:
      version: v2
Apply destination rules:

kubectl apply -f destination-rules.yaml
